\N<Customer>O-oi... Are you really sure it's okay? Is Segi-san really
going to come here...?

\N<Shopkeeper>Yeah, there's no mistake. That's the deal we
have.

\N<Customer>...Even so, you're making us wait quite a bit.

\N<Shopkeeper>She probably needs to prepare herself mentally. Even though
she's in disguise, she's going to be exposing her skin
openly to men other than her husband.

\N<Customer>H-hey... The guy in the back! Don't push! It's cramped
enough as it is!

\N<Customer>Ugh, shut up...! I can't see well from here! And she's not
even here yet...!

\N<Customer>That's none of my concern. If that's the case, you should
pay more money like I did...!
\N<Customer>What did you say...!?

\N<Shopkeeper>Heh, stop the fighting. Don't worry, she'll definitely
appear soon.

The cramped room was stifling with the heat of the
gendarmes. Amidst it, they were whispering and discussing
something.

\N<Customer>Hey, hey... We've been waiting quite a while, haven't we...?
Is it really okay?
\N<Customer>...Be quiet. I hear something...
\N<Customer>R-Really... Segi-san...! Segi-san has come...!

\N<Customer>Ha, haha... This is unbearable, isn't it?! Can this even be
happening?! She's going to change clothes just beyond that
mirror from now on, right...?!
i_1_セギ04b
\N<Customer>Ahh!!??

In front of the excited men, the figure of Segi with a
melancholic expression appeared before the large mirror.
\N<Customer>S-She's here! She really came...!

Contrary to the men's joy and anticipation, Segi's
expression on the other side of the mirror was gloomy. And
there was no sign that she realized she was being exposed to
prying eyes through the trick mirror.
i_1_セギ04c
\N<Customer>O-oi! What's going on?! I can't see well at all!

Segi on the other side of the mirror reached for her
clothes. With the sound of fabric rustling, her body was
exposed before the men's eyes.

However, the trick mirror remained fogged up. This was far
from satisfying the men's desires.

\N<Customer>It's visible but this is just teasing! Shopkeeper, what's
going on?! Hey!
i_1_セギ04d

\N<Shopkeeper>This is... unexpected. Unlucky, it seems like a malfunction
of the equipment.

\N<Customer>Don't mess with me! Unlucky?! We paid money for this! Is a
malfunction supposed to be an excuse?!

\N<Shopkeeper>I get it, I get it. I'll make sure it's fixed by next time.
And I'll make it free for you then.

\N<Customer>Next time?! Is there definitely going to be a next
time?!
\N<Shopkeeper>Yeah, I promise.

\N<Customer>Tch... Damn it! Getting our hopes up for nothing... Listen
here...! Make sure you fix the malfunction by next
time...!

\N<Shopkeeper>Heh, don't be so impatient. Surely she will come again
soon... your wife, that is.
\N<Customer>Really? Are you sure? How can you be so certain?

\N<Shopkeeper>This is a tavern. Given the nature of this place, all sorts
of stories come to my ears. Including those of Ryuda's
folks.
\N<Customer>...?

\N<Shopkeeper>She'll definitely come again. So you guys should keep coming
to the shop frequently and spend your money,
alright?

\N<Customer>You're a greedy one... But I'll trust you this
time.
\N<Shopkeeper>Yeah... Look forward to it.
